Troubleshooting Tips
Container won't start:

Check logs: docker logs <container-name>
Verify Dockerfile syntax
Ensure all dependencies are in requirements.txt
Cannot connect to Redis:

Verify Redis container is running: docker ps
Check network connectivity: docker network inspect app-network
Ensure REDIS_HOST environment variable is set correctly
Port already in use:

Check existing processes: sudo lsof -i :5000
Stop conflicting containers: docker stop <container-name>
Use different port mapping: -p 5001:5000
Image build fails:

Ensure you're in correct directory
Check file paths in COPY commands
Verify requirements.txt exists
Worker not processing tasks:

Check worker logs for errors
Verify Redis connection
Test Redis manually: docker exec -it redis redis-cli
Cleanup
# Stop all containers
docker stop api worker redis

# Remove containers
docker rm api worker redis

# Remove network
docker network rm app-network

# Optional: Remove images
docker rmi task-api:v1 task-worker:v1
